comments[37]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:58:11.171Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: SDK-first inventory contains generic query and lifecycle promotion slices but no stable typed relationship registry plus bounded graph algorithm API; this is a new promotion slice under pm-96h7 and relates to pm-usfg."
  "2026-07-14T07:46:26.495Z",codex-gpt5-root,"Evidence: delivered the first broad public graph foundation: versioned built-in/custom relationship registry, alias compatibility, immutable in-memory index construction from item metadata, deterministic adjacency/closure/reverse-impact/shortest-path/subgraph queries with cancellation and explicit cost/truncation metadata, SDK barrel/docs, and validate integration. Packed tarball consumer proved a custom company owns graph plus real CLI lifecycle. Full repository run passed 286 files/5664 tests; focused all-source coverage for relationships.ts is 100/100/100/100. Remaining event mutation, durable incremental index, snapshot/streaming, MCP projection, and million-item scale acceptance stay on this feature, so it will return to open rather than be falsely closed."
  "2026-07-14T08:15:26.847Z",codex-root,"PR #554 review evidence: addressed all ten first-round findings across construction complexity/performance, bounded closure/path truncation, malformed/custom lifecycle dependencies, immutable payload schemas, canonical dependency conversion, inverse-kind filters, generated changelog accuracy, and duplicate-edge documentation. Focused relationship coverage is exact 100/100/100/100; full repository run passed 286 files and 5664 tests before the final single branch regression was added. The broader durable event/index acceptance remains open."
  "2026-07-14T08:27:50.810Z",codex-root,"PR #554 second-round evidence: deduplicated bidirectional candidate accounting, changed induced subgraph assembly from whole-graph O(E) filtering to bounded adjacency-index work, enforced alias identifiers, and restored the no-guessing contract for unregistered dependency kinds. Registered custom ordering remains supported by the SDK registry; CLI extension-registry injection belongs to the remaining adapter acceptance. Focused tests pass 95/95, relationship coverage is exact 100/100/100/100, ESLint and build pass."
  "2026-07-14T08:39:28.907Z",codex-root,"PR #554 third-round evidence: registry resolution, graph nodes/endpoints, and item-derived relationships now defend malformed runtime input with precise behavior; item references normalize whitespace while preserving canonical case-sensitive identifiers. Lifecycle graph construction accepts an injected RelationshipKindRegistry, with tests proving custom ordering kinds participate and custom associative kinds do not. Focused relationship coverage is exact 100/100/100/100; 95 focused tests, ESLint, and build pass."
  "2026-07-14T08:48:53.052Z",codex-root,"PR #554 fourth-round evidence: closure and shortest-path visitedNodes now count dequeued frontier nodes, max-depth truncation inspects and counts only unseen reachable work, and induced subgraphs apply canonical/inverse kind filters during indexed edge reconstruction. Relationship coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100; focused tests, ESLint, and build pass."
  "2026-07-14T09:00:21.525Z",codex-root,"PR #554 fifth-round evidence: payload schema freezing is cycle-safe, inverse identifiers normalize and validate with the registry grammar, adjacency avoids duplicate uniqueness work, and BFS resolves neighbors once per dequeued node while checking limits before visit marking. Relationship coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100; ESLint and build pass."
  "2026-07-14T09:23:45.257Z",codex-root,"PR #554 final-round evidence: shortestPath now uses a parent map and reconstructs only the winning route, reducing traversal state to O(V) while preserving case-sensitive item identity; schema freeze assertions now fail on missing structure. Focused 95 tests pass, relationship coverage is exact 100/100/100/100, ESLint and build pass."
  "2026-07-14T09:43:36.284Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: continue the merged registry/query foundation with immutable attributable relationship events, replayable snapshots, continuation/index seams, and thin public-SDK consumption. All-status duplicate review reused the canonical graph lineage; no parallel item was created."
  "2026-07-14T10:19:33.062Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: added explicit ordering precedence to the extensible relationship registry; immutable deterministic graph node enumeration; and an append-only attributable RelationshipEventLog with stable relationship identities, optimistic version checks, add/remove/supersede events, cardinality validation, immutable replay snapshots by version/time, and opaque cursor pagination. Public packed SDK consumer proof imported @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk in a fresh project and replayed a custom company owns relationship plus delivery dependencies successfully."
  "2026-07-14T10:48:29.843Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 1 evidence: accepted and resolved graph-kernel findings by caching the immutable sorted node snapshot, introducing explicit source_parent/target_parent hierarchy orientation, and documenting built-in versus custom semantics. Repeated nodes() identity and hierarchy validation regressions pass; full repository coverage is exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T11:06:16.950Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 2 evidence: added the public indexed incidentEdges() graph primitive and changed relationship append normalization from whole-universe graph reconstruction to validated two-endpoint normalization. Malformed source and target inputs are covered; immutable incident snapshots are deterministic and frozen."
  "2026-07-14T11:44:57.342Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 4 evidence: event cardinality checks now stream the active map with an excluded relationship id and no whole-map or comparable-array copies; incident edges use a linear merge of sorted indexes while correctly deduplicating undirected edges and self-loops. Fresh installed-package supersede proof and exact 100/100/100/100 coverage pass."
  "2026-07-14T12:10:43.200Z",codex-gpt5,"Evidence for PR #556 final review tranche: replaced O(R) active-edge cardinality scans with maintained O(1) identity/outgoing-one/incoming-one indexes covering add, supersede, remove, and slot reuse; timestamp snapshots now replay the contiguous append-sequence prefix through the last qualifying timestamp even for non-monotonic event time. Regression tests cover non-monotonic replay, empty pre-history snapshots, active-count independence, and cardinality-slot reuse. Verification: 287/287 files and 5,683/5,683 tests passed with exact 100% statements/branches/functions/lines (36,684/26,338/7,410/35,813); lint, typecheck, jscpd zero clones, 100% docstring gate, package boundary, and token-budget gates passed. Fresh packed @unbrained/pm-cli consumer appended 10,000 relationships in 207 ms and correctly materialized a 10,002-event non-monotonic snapshot. Gemini threads PRRT_kwDORSgRDc6Qutwn and PRRT_kwDORSgRDc6Qutwt were reacted to, replied to, and resolved. Item remains open for later durable-adapter work; active implementation is complete for this tranche."
  "2026-07-14T12:42:11.194Z",codex-root,"Live external-state orientation 2026-07-14: main is clean at merged PR #556; open PRs #538/#539/#540/#541/#552 are Dependabot updates; GitHub APIs report zero open Dependabot security alerts, zero code-scanning alerts, and zero secret-scanning alerts. v2026.7.14 and npm 2026.7.14 are current; the latest auto-release run on unchanged main skipped as expected while CI, Docs, Security, and CodeQL succeeded. Existing GH-522 nightly failures map to pm-b24b and pm-u5zr, so no duplicate was created."
  "2026-07-14T12:58:58.495Z",codex-root,"Implementation progress: added lock-serialized durable RelationshipEventStore JSONL replay plus native deps format=context through shared SDK, CLI, MCP, and generated contract surfaces. Corrupt JSONL/sequence rejection, concurrent appends, removal replay, bounds, cursor continuation, and summary projection are covered."
  "2026-07-14T13:07:52.319Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: exact full coverage passed 287 files / 5,687 tests at 100/100/100/100. A packed-package consumer registered a custom company/VCS-style owns relationship, appended it through RelationshipEventStore, reopened the JSONL stream, and queried the persisted graph successfully. Concurrent-store, corrupt JSONL, sequence-drift, unreadable-path, tracker-root containment, traversal, and absolute-path escape tests pass."
  "2026-07-14T13:16:53.526Z",codex-root,"Observability closeout: release gates confirm telemetry health (0.3% finish errors, zero missing error codes). The only gate blockers are external handled Sentry issues PM-CLI-29/pm-7n5a and PM-CLI-2B/pm-d4ns; neither stack or implementation belongs to this relationship SDK bundle."
  "2026-07-14T13:17:44.146Z",codex-root,"This implementation tranche completes the built-in durable JSONL adapter and native deps context integration across SDK/CLI/MCP contracts. The canonical feature remains open for migration/backfill, pluggable incremental indexes, JSONL/stream projections, deeper crash recovery, and million-item storage validation."
  "2026-07-14T14:01:59.298Z",codex-gpt5,"Review-round evidence for PR #559: fixed Greptile's cross-instance stale-read finding and CodeRabbit's bare '..' containment finding. RelationshipEventStore snapshot/page now refresh from the durable JSONL stream before materialization, path validation rejects both '..' and descendant escapes, and real two-store regressions cover visibility. Fresh packed consumer proof observed durable version 2 after a second instance appended. Full suite: 287 files, 5689 tests, exact coverage 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T14:37:40.049Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 review round 2 evidence: removed the stale synchronous store version surface and added async currentVersion(), which reloads and validates durable JSONL before returning the optimistic sequence. Cross-instance tests prove currentVersion/snapshot/page all observe another store's completed append; fresh packed consumer observed version 2. Full suite: 287 files, 5689 tests, exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T15:13:07.359Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 review round 3 evidence: durable currentVersion/snapshot/page refreshes now acquire the same relationship-store lock as append, preventing torn-tail reads; open creates then validates a new tracker root and rejects symlinked roots or existing path components. Unit regressions cover fresh roots, target symlinks, and root symlinks; fresh packed consumer passes."
  "2026-07-14T15:30:08.551Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 final read-race evidence: RelationshipEventStore.open now acquires the same store lock before its initial JSONL replay, completing lock coverage across open, currentVersion, snapshot, page, and append. Focused test, typecheck, strict static quality, full exact coverage, and freshly packed consumer pass."
  "2026-07-14T15:54:37.032Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 review round 5 evidence: relationship event cursors now carry an opaque producer snapshot token, and RelationshipEventLog replays continuation against that immutable version prefix. A second durable store can append version 3 between pages while the original cursor deterministically completes version 2; cursorless reads still refresh to version 3. Fresh packed SDK consumer proves the cross-writer contract with zero npm vulnerabilities."
  "2026-07-14T16:24:54.670Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #559 CodeRabbit security evidence: every durable read/write now reacquires the shared store lock, revalidates tracker-root containment and every existing path component, and opens the event file with O_NOFOLLOW. A post-open symlink swap is rejected by currentVersion, snapshot, page, and append; a freshly packed consumer proves the external target remains unchanged. Repeated lock configuration is centralized in a three-call-site helper."
  "2026-07-17T06:12:39.690Z",maintainer-agent,"Adapter-acceptance progress via the pm-8xr8 lane (2026-07-17): the graph kernel gained the public neighborEdges(id, options) primitive (deterministic neighbor rows paired with their connecting edges - the seam context explanation needed), and the native CLI/MCP graph-context adapter now exposes direction and registry-validated kind filters end-to-end with contract/schema/completion parity. Remaining canonical scope here is unchanged: durable incremental indexes, migration/backfill, JSONL/stream projections, deeper crash recovery, and million-item storage validation (pm-m2il matrix)."
  "2026-07-17T13:10:35.703Z",codex-root,"Implementation progress: completed the wide graph SDK continuation with shared workspace assembly, registry-aware hierarchy and ordering traversals, bounded simple-path enumeration, policy-aware graph governance, public actionability exports, and thinner CLI adapters. Focused tests, strict static quality, package-boundary, token-budget, and docs gates pass."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:19.921Z",codex-root,"Verification evidence: linked graph/relationship tests passed 4/4; full repository coverage passed 5,798 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; lint, zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, token-budget, typecheck, secrets, npx pack, and 88-command dogfood gates passed. Fresh packed @unbrained/pm-cli consumer modeled a VCS commit DAG and company ownership hierarchy through public SDK traversal/path APIs. This tranche is complete; canonical feature remains open for the explicitly recorded incremental-index, migration/backfill, stream projection, crash-recovery, and million-item scope."
  "2026-07-17T14:12:23.347Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 5843a507-bc02-480c-b73f-b95c37e34b46: path enumeration now carries a per-path Set for O(1) cycle checks instead of linear node scans; bounded deterministic semantics are unchanged. Full repository passes 5,800 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-17T14:26:01.994Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile re-review 311185a2-1f96-41a9-b26d-6055ec75cd16 rated the corrected bundle 5/5 safe to merge with no review comments and confirmed all four prior findings resolved. Its only interface-clarity note was addressed: GraphTraversalOptions now omits generic direction because hierarchy/order orientation is registry-defined; GraphPathOptions retains direction where it is meaningful. Typecheck, ESLint, and focused traversal tests pass."
  "2026-07-17T15:21:09.260Z",codex-root,"PR #579 review round 1: fixed canonical ID normalization for padded workspace items; made path truncation metadata probe one extra result and inspect depth-boundary continuations; applied abort/kind/maxPaths controls to zero-length paths; and retained strict complexity via a dedicated non-zero enumeration stage."
  "2026-07-17T16:10:54.378Z",codex-sdk-graph,"PR #579 review round 2 evidence: workspace assembly now accepts the caller's RelationshipKindRegistry, preserves registered VCS/company/custom edges through normalization, and filters malformed or empty legacy item IDs at the public SDK boundary. Regression proof covers custom commits_to assembly plus null, missing, numeric, and empty IDs. Full repository coverage passes 298 files / 5,802 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
  "2026-07-17T16:34:00.153Z",codex-sdk-graph,"PR #579 final hosted review evidence: enumerateRelationshipPaths now rejects NaN, infinite, fractional, and negative maxPaths, maxVisitedPaths, and maxDepth values before either zero-length or non-zero traversal branch. Regression coverage exercises all three public bounds and invalid value families. Full repository coverage passes 298 files / 5,803 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; typecheck, ESLint, zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
  "2026-07-17T17:00:01.945Z",codex-sdk-graph,"PR #579 final Gemini evidence: workspace assembly now adds case-deduplicated missing endpoints to the canonical-ID map before projecting parent, blocker, and dependency edges, so case variants converge on one placeholder without dropped edges. Semantic hierarchy/ordering kind filters now flow into neighborEdges, reducing inspected-edge work while preserving inverse-kind behavior. Behavioral regressions prove two case-variant missing references retain both edges and a filtered hierarchy walk inspects only its family. Full coverage passes 298 files / 5,804 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-17T19:21:45.879Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress (graph-query-surface lane): new workspace-facing pm graph command with eight subcommands (ancestors/descendants/predecessors/successors/paths/impact/analyze/audit) as a thin adapter over the public SDK graph toolkit — one assembleWorkspaceRelationshipGraph call per invocation, case-insensitive root resolution excluding missing placeholders, counts-first envelopes with explicit truncated+cost metadata, --summary suppression, cursor continuation, and registry-validated --kind filters. Wired end-to-end: CLI registration, PmClient.graph + module-level graph(), MCP pm_graph narrow tool (29-tool surface), action schema/flag/option/parameter contracts, bash/zsh/fish completions, contracts fixture regen, and docs (COMMANDS.md Graph Queries, RELATIONSHIP_GRAPH.md native-adapter paragraph, SDK.md, AGENT_GUIDE.md). runtime.ts input-normalization helpers partitioned into sdk/runtime-input.ts (~450 lines freed below the file-size gate, restoring yh8r headroom)."
  "2026-07-17T20:19:38.230Z",maintainer-agent,"Graph-query-surface tranche verification (commit a3b47c97): 301 test files / 5,842 tests pass at exact 100/100/100/100 coverage; eslint, jscpd zero-clone, 100% docstring, package-boundary, token-budget, and typecheck gates pass. pm graph now spans 11 subcommands; manual temp-workspace acceptance covered CLI (release DAG: dominators ranked the gating publish item, redundancy flagged the shortcut blocked_by edge with witness), PmClient.graph, and raw SDK analytics on a custom commits_to VCS registry (c1->c3 transitive shortcut detected, dominator tree correct). Coverage hardening added run-defensive.spec (non-TypeError kernel failures rethrown unchanged) and empty-workspace zero-value envelopes."
  "2026-07-17T20:31:03.205Z",maintainer-agent,"Pre-push Greptile review 009b6487-99a0-489e-9bbb-c3ee280a0d66 (confidence 3/5, three findings, all fixed): (P1) pm_graph MCP subcommand enum was hardcoded at 8 values so communities/redundancy/dominators were unreachable over MCP transport — GRAPH_SUBCOMMAND_VALUES moved into sdk/cli-contracts/enum-contracts.ts as the single source (tool-definitions stays dependency-light since it already imports that module), run.ts re-exports for barrel compatibility, contracts fixture regenerated (the stale enum had propagated into full.json), and a handshake parity test now locks the schema enum to the shared contract. (P1) GraphCommunitiesResult gained the explicit truncated flag every sibling envelope carries (community_count vs sample bound). (P2) O(k^2) linear dedup scans replaced with Sets in collectTransitiveFamilies (per-family adjacency now Set-built, sorted once per scan) and indexReachableSubgraph. 95 affected tests pass; lint/static/boundary/token gates re-verified."
notes[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:19:35.648Z",codex-gpt5,"Remaining canonical scope after this PR: durable storage adapters, native CLI/MCP graph query integration, migration/backfill, and million-item storage validation; keep feature open."
  "2026-07-17T10:22:56.686Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation constraints recorded 2026-07-17 (review pass #96), two hard facts for whoever claims this slice. (1) src/sdk/runtime.ts gate headroom is 2 lines (census on pm-yh8r) — this slice's registry/graph-query exports CANNOT go through runtime.ts; ship the runtime partition first/with it, or route the new primitives through a dedicated subpath module (precedent: PR#571-lane sdk/test + sdk/diagnostics folders; sdk/query/ is the natural home). (2) Perf shape to fix while building the query primitives: pm deps --format context today assembles the FULL workspace RelationshipGraph + dangling-reference collection on every call (assembleDepsRelationshipGraph in src/sdk/dependencies.ts calls collectDanglingDependencyReferences + RelationshipGraph.fromItems over ALL items before bounding) — bounded output but unbounded assembly cost, O(all items) per invocation. The adjacency/bounded-subgraph primitives owned here are the natural place to make assembly incremental/indexed so bounded queries stop paying full-workspace cost; pm-m2il's scale matrix (query-budget axis) will measure it, pm-9rxu bl8x cache contract (CACHE_VERSION) is the substrate if an index is persisted."
  "2026-07-17T20:01:23.576Z",maintainer-agent,"Graph-query-surface lane continuation (2026-07-17, second tranche): pm graph grew communities/redundancy/dominators subcommands (11 total) as thin adapters over new sdk/graph/analytics.ts; hierarchyParentEndpoint/orderingPredecessorEndpoint promoted to module exports so analytics reuses traversal's semantic-orientation logic (single implementation, no clones). runtime.ts lost two now-unused runtime-input imports (isRecord, updateManyUpdateOptionsFromFlat) flagged by eslint after the partition. Test-lane fix: mcp-dynamic-package-actions impact assertion assumed pm_deps options.dep mutates — it never does (read projection); edge now created via pm_update, and the silent nested-options drop is filed as pm-upi0."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T07:46:27.146Z",codex-gpt5-root,"A storage-independent relationship registry is the semantic boundary: algorithms must consume ordering/hierarchy flags rather than infer meaning from labels, while durable event/index implementations can remain interchangeable."
  "2026-07-14T10:02:20.502Z",codex-gpt5,Optimistic append sequences plus cursor fingerprints bind every page and snapshot to a coherent immutable relationship history; durable adapters can persist the same event contract without coupling graph semantics to storage.
